## Cross-platform release

The `.github/workflows/release.yml` workflow drives a tauri-action
3-OS matrix:

| Job runner       | Outputs                                |
|------------------|----------------------------------------|
| `windows-latest` | `{{ slug_name }}_<version>_x64_en-US.msi`, `.exe` |
| `macos-14`       | `{{ slug_name }}.app`, `{{ slug_name }}_<version>_aarch64.dmg` |
| `ubuntu-22.04`   | `{{ slug_name }}_<version>_amd64.deb`, `.AppImage`, `.rpm` |

Cut a release locally:

```bash
git tag app-v0.1.0
git push origin app-v0.1.0
# release.yml triggers; it uploads artifacts to a draft GitHub Release.
```

