## Auto-update channel

The scaffold wires `tauri-plugin-updater` and ships a placeholder
public-key envelope in `src-tauri/tauri.conf.json`. **Operator
workflow:**

```bash
# 1. Generate a minisign key pair (one-shot, save the private key
#    to your secret store вЂ” NOT the repo)
pnpm tauri signer generate -w ~/.tauri/{{ slug_name }}.key

# 2. Paste the printed PUBLIC key into src-tauri/tauri.conf.json
#    -> bundle.updater.pubkey

# 3. Set the manifest endpoint to your CDN
#    -> bundle.updater.endpoints
#       (e.g. "https://releases.example.com/{{ '{{target}}' }}/{{ '{{current_version}}' }}")

# 4. After each `tauri build`, sign the produced binary with your
#    private key and publish a `latest.json` manifest pointing to
#    the signed asset. Tauri's plugin verifies the minisign signature
#    on the client BEFORE applying any update.
```

The signing private key + password live in CI secrets
(`TAURI_SIGNING_PRIVATE_KEY` / `TAURI_SIGNING_PRIVATE_KEY_PASSWORD`)
and never appear in the repo.
